'''Marina Fitch''' (born [[April 11]], [[1950s#1957|1957]]) is an [[Wikipedia:Americans|American]] author of Science Fiction and Fantasy.<ref name="Locus" /> She wrote "[[Let Us Prey: The Whiphid's Tale]]" in collaboration with [[Mark Budz]] as part of ''[[Tales from Jabba's Palace]]'', which was published by [[Bantam Spectra]] in [[January]] [[1996]].

Fitch graduated from the [[Wikipedia:University of California, Santa Cruz|University of California, Santa Cruz]] in [[1981]], and her first short story was published in [[Wikipedia:L. Ron Hubbard|L. Ron Hubbard's]] [[Wikipedia:Writers and Illustrators of the Future|Writers and Illustrators of the Future]] in [[1986]]. Not long afterward, she briefly worked for [[Kristine Kathryn Rusch]] at [[Wikipedia:Pulphouse Publishing|Pulphouse Publishing]]. Fitch has written such novels as ''The Seventh Heart'' and ''The Border''.<ref name="Locus" />

